    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://newyork.craigslist.org/que/ret/6045366483.html"></div>
        </div>
<b>Amerivents, a leading Hospitality Management Company is seeking a candidate for our Assistant Cafe Manager position for our Cafe operation located in Flushing, Queens. The Assistant Cafe Manager is responsible for managing and operating the day-to-day functions of the Cafe. He/she manages and oversees the Cafe staff to ensure members receive the highest level of quality and customer service possible. </b><br>
<br>
This position will work together with another Cafe Manager, and will be responsible for hiring, firing, training and scheduling a cafe team. Must be able to manage and motivate others to succeed.<br>
<br>
<u><b>Tentative Schedule</u></b><br>
Wednesday thru Sunday- daytime hours<br>
** With exceptions for catered events and company needs on larger days<br>
<br>
<u><b>Essential Duties: </u></b><br>
-Serve as lead customer service contact for guests<br>
-Responsible for some drop off catering orders within facility where Cafe is located<br>
-Establish, monitor and analyze Cafe budget<br>
-Track and manage Cafe profitability<br>
-Manage vendors, maintain and order inventory items<br>
-Responsible for keeping Cafe clean, neat, orderly<br>
<br>
<u><b>Required Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:</u></b><br>
-Highly motivated, able to work independently and lead a team<br>
-Strong customer service experience needed<br>
-Excellent communication and interpersonal skills<br>
-Strong organizational and administrative skills a must<br>
-Ability to motivate others<br>
-Ability to lift heavy boxes and be on your feet for long portions of the day<br>
-Must be available to work days, evenings and weekends<br>
-Ability to work a flexible schedule and work an average of 40-50 hours per week.<br>
<br>
<u><b>Preferred Education and Experience:</u></b><br>
-At least 2 years professional experience in food and beverage environment preferred; experience in cafe or gourmet take out establishment strongly preferred<br>
-Experience in operations management role<br>
-Culinary background a plus<br>
- Food Handlers Certification<br>
-High School or GED required, Bachelors Degree preferred<br>
-CPR, First Aid and AED certifications (must be obtained within 60 days of hire)<br>
<br>
We are an Equal Opportunity Employer (EOE). Applicants are considered for employment without regard to age, race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, disability, veteran status, or any other basis prohibited by law.<br>
Benefits Include Medical insurance/Dental insurance, and Paid Time Off<br>
    </section>

